fields.title: About This App
fields.content:
## Welcome to this app. ##

Please note that this app is an early release and is not yet fully functional.  However it is usable and new users are welcome to try it and provide feedback on how useful it is.

This app has a very simple purpose, which is to help project / programme managers to easily create a single page visualisation of a project plan.

The app allows you to upload a project plan - currently in one of a number of supported Excel formats - and create a visualisation of that plan by placing activities from the plan into a visual.  

The key features are:  


- You can structure the visualisation into swimlanes and place activities in a specific swimlane.
- You can choose which activities from your plan appear in the visual.  The idea is if you have a long plan with hundreds of rows, you can pick and choose the right subset of activities to place on your visualisation to provide a high level view of the plan which fits on a page.
- Activities can appear on the same line if required so you can use best use of space and provide visual cues by placing related sequential tasks together on a line.
- You can style each activity individually in terms of the shape used, the colour of the activity, the colour and size of the font used for the text.
- The text for an activity can be aligned to the left or right edge and can flow outside the shape, so that short activities can still be labelled clearly.
- One or more timelines can be added to the top of the visual showing months, quarters (and shortly other timeline intervals).

The workflow for using the app is:

1. Create an Excel export of your project plan in one of the supported formats.
2. Upload the Excel plan to the app.
3. Create a new visual from the plan.
